#Braching Statements 

git branch  
Displays all branches in the repository.  
The current active branch is highlighted.

git branch feature-name  
Creates a new branch without switching to it. 
Useful for starting separate work safely.

git checkout feature-name  
Switches from the current branch to another branch.  
Used to work on a different feature or version.

git checkout -b feature-name  
Creates a new branch and switches to it immediately.  
Useful for quickly starting new feature work.

git merge feature-name  
Merges another branch into the current branch.  
Used to combine completed work into main.

git branch -d feature-name  
Deletes a branch after it has been merged.  
Helps keep the repository clean.

git branch -m old-name new-name  
Renames an existing branch.  
Useful when changing branch naming conventions.
